### Why this works (Cloudflare Zero Trust)

`src/utils/cf_patch.py` monkey-patches `requests.Session.send` to inject `CF-Access-Client-Id` and `CF-Access-Client-Secret` headers on every request. This means **you can use the public `https://clearml.multiagent.vision` URL** ŌĆö no need for Tailscale IP.

CF credentials are hardcoded as defaults in `cf_patch.py` (and also in `.env`):
- `CF_ACCESS_CLIENT_ID=31ac6b5b8358a3b78703ba425a5eab14.access`
- `CF_ACCESS_CLIENT_SECRET=f739f3dc336681b46781f668c6d127462450d11d06c9a486828638909b59d5ed`

